<p>GDP growth: 6.2% GDP: $189bn (PPP: $233bn) Inflation: 6.0% Population: 16.6m GDP per head: $11,380 (PPP: $14,040)</p>

<p>Nursultan Nazarbayev, in charge since Soviet times, will stay there thanks to a mix of patronage, repression and oil-fired economic growth. Living standards are rising, unemployment is modest and the opposition enfeebled. Political reforms mean a second party will enter the legislature in the 2012 elections, but it will probably be a stooge for the government. Economic growth will slow a little from 2011.</p>

